HEADWORD: Exprobrate
<hw>Ex"pro*brate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exprobratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exprobrare</ets>; <ets>ex</ets>
out + <ets>probrum</ets> a shameful or disgraceful act.]</ety> <def>To
charge upon with reproach; to upbraid.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

